oai_dc:dc.dc:title: PSITTACINE RETRIEVAL PROGRAM GUIDELINES PUBLISHED
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: n/a, n/a
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The California Department of Foodand Agriculture has published recommendedguidelines for the retrieval of the IndianRingneck Parrakeet, Nanday Conure andCanary-Wing Bee Bee, all of which areconfirmed as having bred in the wild . Theprogram will be given a one year trialperiod, during which time the state's proposedprohibition on the possession andsale of said birds will be postponed. If theprogram succeeds, the contemplated restrictionswill be shelved.
